<TITLE> Wazed Miah is 'critically ill' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka May 6 (bdnews24.com)Dr M A Wazed Miah, husband of prime minister Sheikh Hasina, is critically ill at the capital's Square Hospital and is suffering for months from multiple complications. No doctor or official at the prime minister's office would say until 5:30pm anything about the Dr Miah's latest condition. But sources with knowledge of his condition said it was 'critical'. Dr Modasser Ali, the prime mister's health affairs adviser, told bdnews24.com, when reached that only the doctor overseeing him will speak on the matter. Prof Sanwar Hossain, who is treating Dr Miah, earlier told bdnews24.com that he was taken to the operating theatre after his condition had worsened. Hasina drove to the hospital just before 3pm to see him. She spent around an hour at the bedside of her husband. She as looking dejected as trudged out of the hospital corridor, helped by her sister, Rehana, at around 3:45pm. A nuclear scientist in his 60s, Dr Miah recently had angioplasty at Mount Elizabeth Hospital in Singapore. He underwent a bypass surgery in 1997. He had long been suffering also from high blood pressure, renal failure, diabetes and asthma. b
